        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <h3>How long does it take to build an estimating database?</h3>
        <p>Plan 3–6 months before your estimating database is working well. The first few estimates take extra time because you're building assemblies from scratch. By 6 months, most of your common cost items are in the library and estimates become significantly faster. The payoff compounds over time.</p>

        <h3>Should I start with a free trial?</h3>
        <p>Always. Estimating workflow is personal — what works for one estimator feels wrong to another. Free trials (Buildxact offers 14 days; Stack offers a trial) let you run a real estimate through the tool before committing. Don't evaluate based on demo alone.</p>

        <h3>What's the biggest mistake when choosing estimating software?</h3>
        <p>Choosing based on features rather than workflow fit. The most feature-rich estimating tool is worthless if it doesn't match how your estimating team works. Focus on the specific workflow — how does takeoff work, how do assemblies get applied, how does the output look — rather than a feature checklist.</p>

